AFFOGATO AL CAFFE’ (COFFEE IN VANILLA ICE CREAM)

ByValentina July 3, 2024December 18, 2024
Jump to Recipe Print Recipe

This treat combines the robust, rich flavors of freshly brewed espresso with the creamy, velvety texture of vanilla ice cream, creating a harmonious symphony of hot and cold sensations that dance across the palate.

Rooted in the traditions of Italian coffee culture, the word “affogato” means “drowned,” an apt description as hot espresso is poured over cold gelato, melting it into an aromatic, lush pool.

Perfect for a quick aperitif or a refined meal finale, Affogato al Caffè is a testament to the beauty of minimalism, where high-quality ingredients shine through with a minimum of embellishment.

 

 

SERVINGS:2

INGREDIENTS:

  • 1 cup strong espresso coffee
  • 1 tablespoon sugar
  • Coffee or vanilla ice cream
  • 1 cup good whiskey

Garnish: (optional)

  • Grated chocolate
  • Coffee beans
  • whipped cream

 

METHOD:

Prepare the hot coffee blend.
– Prepare 1 cup of strong espresso coffee using your preferred method (espresso machine, stove or coffee maker).
– While the coffee is still very hot, add 1 tablespoon of sugar to the coffee and stir well to dissolve the sugar.
– Once the sugar is dissolved, pour in 1 cup of good whiskey. Stir again to combine the whisky with the coffee and sugar. The whiskey adds a deep, warming flavor that complements the bitterness of the coffee.

Make sure the coffee is hot when you pour it over the ice cream to ensure that the ice cream melts slightly, creating a perfect blend of textures and flavors.

Prepare the ice cream
– In each serving glass or bowl, place one or two scoops of coffee or vanilla ice cream. The ice cream will serve as a cool, creamy base for the hot coffee mixture.
– Use a generous scoop of ice cream to achieve a balanced consistency when pouring the hot coffee mixture over it.

You can use coffee-flavored ice cream for a more intense experience, or vanilla ice cream if you prefer a milder flavor that lets the coffee and whiskey shine through.

Pour in the hot coffee mixture
– Carefully pour the hot coffee and whiskey mixture over the ice cream in each glass. The hot liquid should gently melt the ice cream, creating a delicious contrast between the cold, creamy ice cream and the hot, rich coffee blend.

Tip: Pour the hot coffee mixture slowly to avoid splattering and ensure even melting of the ice cream.

 

Garnish (optional)

– For a decorative and flavorful touch, garnish the Affogato with grated chocolate, coffee granules or a dollop of whipped cream.
– The grated chocolate adds a rich cocoa flavor that goes beautifully with the coffee and ice cream.
– Coffee beans can be sprinkled over the surface for a sophisticated touch and to enhance the coffee aroma.
– Whipped cream adds a light, fluffy texture and extra sweetness that balances the bold flavors of coffee and whiskey.

You can also experiment with other toppings, such as a dusting of cocoa powder or a drizzle of caramel, to give a unique twist to the classic.

 

Serve and enjoy

– Serve immediately while the ice cream is still slightly melted and the coffee blend is hot, to achieve the perfect balance of temperature and flavor in every bite.
– Enjoy your Coffee Affogato as a delicious dessert or as a special treat after a meal!

 

Key Notes:

– The key to this dessert is the contrast between the hot coffee and the cold ice cream. Be sure to serve the coffee blend immediately after brewing for optimal effect.
– You can adjust the amount of whiskey to suit your taste or replace it with another distillate, such as a coffee liqueur, to achieve a different flavor profile.

Affogato Al Caffe’ Recipe

Print Recipe Pin Recipe
Servings 2
Calories 230 kcal

Ingredients
  

INGREDIENTS:

  • 1 cup strong espresso coffee
  • 1 tablespoon sugar
  • Coffee or vanilla ice cream
  • 1 cup good whiskey

Garnish: (optional)

  • Grated chocolate
  • Coffee beans
  • whipped cream

Instructions
 

Prepare the hot coffee blend.

  • – Prepare 1 cup of strong espresso coffee using your preferred method (espresso machine, stove or coffee maker).
  • – While the coffee is still very hot, add 1 tablespoon of sugar to the coffee and stir well to dissolve the sugar.
  • – Once the sugar is dissolved, pour in 1 cup of good whiskey. Stir again to combine the whisky with the coffee and sugar. The whiskey adds a deep, warming flavor that complements the bitterness of the coffee.
  • Make sure the coffee is hot when you pour it over the ice cream to ensure that the ice cream melts slightly, creating a perfect blend of textures and flavors.

Prepare the ice cream

  • – In each serving glass or bowl, place one or two scoops of coffee or vanilla ice cream. The ice cream will serve as a cool, creamy base for the hot coffee mixture.
  • – Use a generous scoop of ice cream to achieve a balanced consistency when pouring the hot coffee mixture over it.

  • – Carefully pour the hot coffee and whiskey mixture over the ice cream in each glass. The hot liquid should gently melt the ice cream, creating a delicious contrast between the cold, creamy ice cream and the hot, rich coffee blend.
  • Tip: Pour the hot coffee mixture slowly to avoid splattering and ensure even melting of the ice cream.

Garnish (optional)

  • – For a decorative and flavorful touch, garnish the Affogato with grated chocolate, coffee granules or a dollop of whipped cream.
  • – The grated chocolate adds a rich cocoa flavor that goes beautifully with the coffee and ice cream.
  • – Coffee beans can be sprinkled over the surface for a sophisticated touch and to enhance the coffee aroma.
  • – Whipped cream adds a light, fluffy texture and extra sweetness that balances the bold flavors of coffee and whiskey.
  • You can also experiment with other toppings, such as a dusting of cocoa powder or a drizzle of caramel, to give a unique twist to the classic.

Serve and enjoy

  • – Serve immediately while the ice cream is still slightly melted and the coffee blend is hot, to achieve the perfect balance of temperature and flavor in every bite.
  • – Enjoy your Coffee Affogato as a delicious dessert or as a special treat after a meal!

Notes

Key Notes:
– The key to this dessert is the contrast between the hot coffee and the cold ice cream. Be sure to serve the coffee blend immediately after brewing for optimal effect.
– You can adjust the amount of whiskey to suit your taste or replace it with another distillate, such as a coffee liqueur, to achieve a different flavor profile.
